decision_conditions:
&lt;p&gt;The use hereby approved shall cease within three months of the date of failure to meet any one of the requirements set out in (i) to (iv) below:-
&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;
i) Within three months of the date of this decision details of the following matters shall have been submitted for the written approval of the local planning authority which shall include a timetable for implementation.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;a) 1:20 detailed drawings and 1:5 sections of the proposed timber windows which include commensurate composite sound insulation performance predictions.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;
b) Details of the proposed refuse store showing the design, location and external appearance to accommodate 3300L for refuse and recycling and 240L for food waste.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;
c) The provision of a policy compliant cycle store.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;d) A scheme for the provision and implementation of flood resilient and resistant construction details and measures for the site and in the basement against surface water flood risk. The scheme shall be carried out in its entirety before the basement is occupied and; constructed and completed in accordance with the approved plans in line with BS 8102:2009 code of practice for &quot;protection of below ground structures against water from the ground&quot; and current best practice where applicable&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;div&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;p&gt;

ii) if within six months of the date of this decision the local planning authority refuse to approve the details or fail to give a decision and have not agreed in writing to an alternative period for a decision to be made, a valid appeal shall have been made to the Secretary of State.
&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;
iii) if an appeal is made in pursuance of (ii) above, that appeal shall have been finally determined and the submitted scheme shall have been approved by the Secretary of State.

iv) the approved scheme shall have been carried out and completed in accordance with the approved timetable.
&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;
REASON: To ensure that adequate waste and cycle provision and appropriate detailing is provided and that the development is adequately protected against flood risk within an appropriate timeframe in the interests of proper planning.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
